As the official record label of melodic dubstep leader Seven Lions, Ophelia Records is a label that promotes independent dance music across a wide range of genres. In just five years, Ophelia has become one of the hottest labels in electronic music thanks to its tight-knit community and ability to connect fans of melodic bass, dubstep, trance, psytrance, drum & bass, house and beyond. Releases have picked up support on flagship playlists across DSPs and radio stations, including the cover of Spotify’s Mint, SiriusXM BPM playlisting and numerous adds to New Music Friday, Dance Rising, danceXL, Bass Arcade and more. With massive releases from acts such as SLANDER, Excision, Kill The Noise, MitiS, Jason Ross, NGHTMRE, Wooli, Trivecta, Blastoyz, Crystal Skies and Last Heroes, Ophelia has reached significant milestones with over 200 catalog releases, multiple #1 iTunes Dance records, sold out showcases and festival takeovers.

Established US talent Jason Ross collaborates with Dia Frampton on ‘Never Alone’, out now on Anjunabeats. 

Jason made his Anjunabeats debut with ‘Elements’ in 2014. He’s since proven himself to be an explorative and versatile artist, turning his hand from trance to melodic bass, melodic dubstep and more. In 2017, he joined forces with Seven Lions and Paul Meany on ‘Higher Love’, one of the label's most popular records to date.

Last year, Jason released his second studio album ‘Atlas’ on Seven Lions’ Ophelia imprint, remixed ARTY & Mat Zo’s legendary Anjunabeats hit ‘Rebound’, and extensively toured across North America. Jason has performed at many of dance music's most prestigious venues, including The Brooklyn Mirage, The Gorge Amphitheatre and Echostage, and graced the stages of festivals such as Tomorrowland, Nocturnal Wonderland, Dreamstate and more, with an impressive run of headline dates to come in San Francisco, New York and Los Angeles.

This year, Jason headlined the mainstage at North America’s largest dance music festival, EDC Las Vegas, and recently rounded up a US tour with Seven Lions, playing shows at The Greek Theatre Berkeley, The Rady Shell, The Pacific Coliseum and beyond. He also dropped three singles on Seven Lions’ Ophelia imprint, which earned support from the likes of NGHTMRE, Farius, ILLENIUM, Gryffin, Mark Sixma and Nathassia, as well as his latest trance-tinged release on Anjunabeats, ‘A Place They Called Home’. 

Dia Frampton has co-written and featured on tracks with world-renowned artists like ILLENIUM, Grammy-nominated EDM legends The Crystal Method, Kaskade, M83 and beyond. She is also a platinum-selling solo artist in Asia, has worked with acclaimed film composer Joseph Trapanese (Tron, Oblivion, Insurgent, and is one half of the duo Meg and Dia). ‘Never Alone’ is the follow up to Jason and Dia’s collaborative singles ‘Stay’ and ‘Before You’, which were both released on Ophelia last year.

Release Date: 27th October 2023
